                            <p class="text10pt" style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><b><i>                              <span style="color: rgb(255,255,255);">                                A personal property appraiser is a trained,                                objective, ethical individual the public can rely                                on to provide a competent, fair assessment of value.                              </span></i></b><br><br>                              <b>Qualifications                                <br>Daniel K. Ewert &#8211; Appraiser / Owner                                <br>Capp Int.<br>Education, Affiliations,                                <br>Certifications &amp; Licenses<br></b>                                <ul class="colored-list">                                  <li>Bachelor of Science Degree in Diesel Engineering Oregon Institute of Technology.</li>                                  <li>Associate Degree Industrial Education Oregon Institute of Technology.</li>                                  <li>Institutionally Trained at the Master Graduate of Personal Property &#8211; Appraiser level for over 10 years.</li>                                  <li>Heavy Equipment, Industrial, Transportation and Manufacturing areas of specialty.</li>                                  <li>Certified USPAP Appraiser Course and Training and annual continuing education current.</li>                                  <li>Graduate of Small Business Fast Track / Greenhouse Growth Venture Kauffman Foundation.</li>                                  <li>Graduate of Western Collage of Auctioneering Billings Montana.</li>                                  <li>Graduate of National Auctioneers Expert Witness in the Courts Course, University of Indiana Law School.</li>                                  <li>Chairman of Planning Commissioner City of Canby, Oregon</li>                                  <li>Completed and passed all State of Oregon Insurance License and Adjusters license testing and requirements. Completed all Course work and testing.</li>                                </ul>                              <b><i>                                <span style="color: rgb(255,255,255);">                                  A personal property appraiser identifies and                                  provides a value for all types of asset                                  groups.</span></i></b></p>
                          </td>
