                          <td colspan="3" width="740" id="Text7" class="TextObject">
                            <p class="text10pt">                              <b>Daniel K. Ewert Appraiser / Owner                                <br>Capp Int.                                <br>                                <br>Experience &amp; Employment History                                <br>Present Capp Int. (Certified Appraisers of Personal Property)</b>                                <br>Company specializing asset and collateral evaluation and liquidation                                <ul class="colored-list">                                  <li>Asset evaluation for Mergers, Collateral verification, Inventory evaluation, Asset Valuations.</li>                                  <li>Facilitate asset recovery or liquidation in the form of pre-qualification of prospective buyers and or sellers.</li>                                  <li>Insure the open communication between client and interested parties to protect against asset shrinkage.</li>                                </ul>                                <br><br>                                <b class="colored-list">Present Finish Line Auctions</b><br>                                <ul class="colored-list">                                  <li>Specializing in Benefit and Charity Auctions in Oregon, Washington, Idaho and Northern California. Events range in size from $30,000.00 to $1,000,000.00.</li>                                  <li>Consulting for non profit and corporate organizations in fundraising efforts.</li>                                  <li>I participate in 30 to 35 events each year.</li>                                </ul>                                <br><br>                                <span class="colored-list">                                  <b>Present:</b>                                <br>Contract Auctioneering and Appraiser                                Services for the following Companies: Brashers                                Northwest Auto Auction Eugene, Brashers Portland                                Auto Auction Portland, Oregon, Pahl Industrial                                Portland Oregon, Vancouver, Canada                                <br><br>                                <b>Appraiser / Auctioneer</b>                                <br>April 2000 to March 2002 Team VanGordon                                Auctioneer. Team VanGordon Auctioneers was a                                diversified Auction and Appraisal company                                located in Oregon. They operated one of the                                largest auction groups in Oregon for many years                                and specialized in the liquidation of assets for                                Lending institutions, Legal Firms, all across                                the Pacific Northwest. They also operated a                                small auto auction. Their appraisal work was                                extensive in Manufacturing, Transportation,                                Agriculture, Industrial and Forestry.                                <br><br>                                Responsibilities Included:                              </span>                                <ul class="colored-list">                                  <li>Staff Appraiser in all areas of Manufacturing, Transportation, Agriculture, Industrial and Forestry.</li>                                  <li>Staff Auctioneer</li>                                  <li>Leader for set up and execution of on and off site liquidations.</li>                                </ul>                            </p>
                            <p class="text10pt"><b>Superior Electrical Contracting Company<br>Owner / Fleet Manager / Operations Manager</b><br>As Working Owner responsibilities included Fleet equipment and field operations for Commercial, Industrial and Residential electrical contracting company operating in Oregon and Washington. SEC employed at its peak 75 Journeyman Electricians and Electrical Engineers and 150 auxiliary employees.<br><br><b>Interstate Service and Equipment Center Inc.<br>Owner / Developer</b><br>This business was developed on the I-5 corridor at Brooks Oregon. Development was centered on the Heavy Truck and Trailer concentration and lack of service facilities in the corridor between Medford Oregon and Portland Oregon. The land was purchased and a 20,000 sq ft service facility was built. This facility included Parts department, Tire department, Oil Change, Component replacement, and Mobile repair services. Due to its location and potential the facility was purchased by Freightliner Corp. / Delmar Benz. </p>
                            <p class="text10pt" style="margin-bottom: 0px;">                              <ul class="colored-list">                                <li>William Scotsman &#8211; Regional Manager in Oregon and Washington for a fleet of over 800 on site modular office and classroom units.</li>                                <li>WW Truck Trailer &#8211; Service Manager for Truck and Trailer repair facility and Tanker weld and repair shop.</li>                                <li>MECO - Service Manager for a rental fleet of heavy equipment that covered Oregon, Washington, Idaho and Northern California</li>                                <li>Distribution Trucking - Fleet Mechanic for Fred Myer Fleet in Oregon and Washington</li>                                <li>Pape&#8217; Caterpillar &#8211; Regional Sales Representative for Oregon and Northern California. Clients included Logging, Fishing, Road Construction, and Under ground.</li>                                <li>Peter Kiewit &amp; Sons &#8211; Project Mechanic in Oregon, California, Washington and Idaho.</li>                              </ul>                            </p>
